1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,646
By the way, this video works great at 1.five times speed for better listening.

2
00:00:05,596 --> 00:00:06,951
Imagine this.

3
00:00:06,951 --> 00:00:09,105
You've built an amazing app.

4
00:00:09,105 --> 00:00:10,625
Users love it.

5
00:00:10,625 --> 00:00:15,375
Then one morning you wake up and your app is on the front page of Hacker News.

6
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:19,653
Suddenly ten million people are trying to use your app at the same time.

7
00:00:19,653 --> 00:00:21,394
Your server crashes.

8
00:00:21,394 --> 00:00:23,701
Your users see error pages.

9
00:00:23,701 --> 00:00:25,480
Your boss is calling.

10
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:28,903
This is the exact problem that Apache Kafka solves.

11
00:00:28,903 --> 00:00:32,500
And if you don't understand it, you WILL face this nightmare.

